A fire incident that engulfed head office of Unity Bank in Victoria Island, Lagos has been brought under control the bank said in a statement. The fire incident occurred early Monday morning. Although the cause of the incident is yet to be ascertained, men of the Lagos State fire service has intervened and brought the situation under control “While the extent is being assessed, we are happy to note that there was no casualty or loss of life as a result of the incident. From the early observations, however, the banking Hall and other strategic business areas were not affected,” the bank said in a statement. “We are grateful to all the agencies and volunteers that supported in bringing the incident under control. Further developments regarding the incident will be communicated as it unfolds.”